                            	  1465: *
                            	  1466: * 'CHKIO' checks the input. If there's no input, it will return
                            	  1467: * to the caller with the Z flag set. If there is input, the Z
                            	  1468: * flag is cleared and the input byte is in D0. However, if a
                            	  1469: * control-C is read, 'CHKIO' will warm-start BASIC and will not
                            	  1470: * return to the caller.
                            	  1471: *
00:0001167A 6100F2EE        	  1472: CHKIO	BSR	GOIN		get input if possible
00:0001167E 6700000E        	  1473: 	BEQ	CHKRET		if Zero, no input
00:00011682 B03C0003        	  1474: 	CMP.B	#CTRLC,D0	is it control-C?
00:00011686 66000006        	  1475: 	BNE	CHKRET		if not
00:0001168A 6000F32A        	  1476: 	BRA	WSTART		if so, do a warm start
00:0001168E 4E75            	  1477: CHKRET	RTS
